quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  36,51,horn blown whereupon they rise ex grave iit their Dominus
  36,52,They dictus Woe to nos. Qui resurrected nos noster decessus? Hoc est quod the Multus Gracious promised messengers est rectus
  36,53,Totus take est 1 blow whereupon they summoned ante nos
  36,54,Ut feria non anima wronged in the parvus Vos paid precisely whatever vos perfecit
  36,55,dwellers Paradise est ut feria happily busy
  36,56,They abide their conjux beautiful shade enjoying comfortable furnishings
  36,57,They habet fruits therein; they habet anything they wish
  36,58,Greetings pax ex Merciful Dominus
  36,59,Prout pro vos O guilty unus vos est set aside
  36,60,perfecit ego non covenant vos O Infans Adam ut vos non worship devil Ut he est tuus ardent enemy
  36,61,Ac ut vos worship Me alone Hoc est rectus path
  36,62,He misled multitudes de vos. Vos non possess any understanding
  36,63,Hoc est Hell promised vos
  36,64,Hodie vos burn it consequence tuus disbelief
  36,65,Feria nos sigillum their mouths their manus feet bear testis everything they perfecit
  36,66,Nos testimentum nos veil their eyes consequently when they seek path they non vide
  36,67,Nos testimentum nos freeze them in locus; ergo they potuit nec move forward nor iit